---
const primitives = [
  {
    name: 'Worker',
    verb: 'hosts the work',
    definition:
      'Anything that opens a WebSocket to the engine and registers functions and triggers. A queue, a scheduler, an HTTP edge, a browser tab, an agent, a sandbox — each is a worker.',
    detail:
      'Workers run anywhere — a laptop, a container, a browser tab, a microVM — in any language that can hold a WebSocket.',
    example: 'mat-iii-worker · iii-state · iii-http',
  },
  {
    name: 'Function',
    verb: 'is the work',
    definition:
      'A named handler inside a worker: payload in, result out. Function IDs follow a service::name convention, so they stay stable across worker restarts and language boundaries.',
    detail:
      'Any worker can call any function through the engine — which is what makes a harness job swappable: register the same ID, replace the layer.',
    example: 'math::add · policy::check_permissions',
  },
  {
    name: 'Trigger',
    verb: 'starts the work',
    definition:
      'What causes a function to run. A trigger has a type — HTTP, cron, queue message, state change, or another function calling trigger — a configuration, and the function ID it invokes.',
    detail:
      'The same function can sit behind several triggers: an HTTP route for the app, a cron for batch runs, a queue for durability.',
    example: 'POST /run → turn::run',
  },
];
---

<section
  class="not-prose my-8 rounded-3xl border border-umai-gray-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-2xl shadow-umai-gray-900/10 dark:border-umai-gray-700 dark:bg-umai-gray-900/80 sm:p-6"
  aria-labelledby="iii-primitives-title"
>
  <div class="mb-6 flex flex-col gap-4 border-b border-umai-gray-200 pb-5 dark:border-umai-gray-700 lg:flex-row lg:items-end lg:justify-between">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <div class="mb-2 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-umai-accent">the iii mental model</div>
      <h3 id="iii-primitives-title" class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-umai-primary dark:text-umai-secondary sm:text-3xl">
        Three primitives, one interface
      </h3>
      <div class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-umai-gray-600 dark:text-umai-gray-300">
        The docs frame it the way Unix framed processes and React framed components: every category
        of software gets a single interface. Workers host the work, functions are the work, triggers
        start it — and the engine routes between them.
      </div>
    </div>
    <a
      href="https://iii.dev/docs/understanding-iii"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-umai-accent/20 bg-umai-accent/10 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-umai-accent transition-colors hover:bg-umai-accent hover:text-white dark:border-umai-accent/30 dark:bg-umai-accent/15"
    >
      iii docs ↗
    </a>
  </div>

  <div class="grid gap-3 lg:grid-cols-3">
    {primitives.map((primitive) => (
      <article class="group relative flex flex-col overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-umai-gray-200 bg-umai-gray-50 p-4 transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:border-umai-accent/50 hover:bg-white hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-umai-accent/10 dark:border-umai-gray-700 dark:bg-umai-gray-800/70 dark:hover:bg-umai-gray-800">
        <div class="absolute inset-x-0 top-0 h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-umai-accent to-umai-accent-light opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-300 group-hover:opacity-100"></div>
        <div class="mb-3 flex items-center justify-between gap-2">
          <h4 class="font-mono text-lg font-bold tracking-tight text-umai-gray-900 dark:text-white">{primitive.name}</h4>
          <span class="rounded-full border border-umai-accent/20 bg-umai-accent/10 px-2.5 py-1 text-[0.65rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-umai-accent dark:border-umai-accent/30 dark:bg-umai-accent/15">
            {primitive.verb}
          </span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm leading-6 text-umai-gray-700 dark:text-umai-gray-200">{primitive.definition}</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-umai-gray-500 dark:text-umai-gray-400">{primitive.detail}</p>
        <p class="mt-auto pt-4">
          <span class="block rounded-lg bg-umai-gray-900 px-3 py-2 font-mono text-[0.7rem] text-green-400 dark:bg-umai-gray-900/90">
            {primitive.example}
          </span>
        </p>
      </article>
    ))}
  </div>

  <div class="mt-3 rounded-2xl border border-umai-accent/25 bg-umai-accent/10 p-4 dark:border-umai-accent/30 dark:bg-umai-accent/15">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-x-3 gap-y-1">
      <h4 class="font-mono text-base font-bold tracking-tight text-umai-gray-900 dark:text-white">Engine</h4>
      <span class="text-[0.65rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-umai-accent">routes between them</span>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-umai-gray-700 dark:text-umai-gray-200">
      The engine is the coordinator: it accepts worker connections over WebSocket, keeps a live
      registry of every registered function and trigger, and routes each invocation to whichever
      worker currently provides that function ID. Nothing talks to anything directly — every arrow
      in the topology is a worker-to-engine connection.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
